        ", who died during an expedition there. The capture of Ascalon by Baldwin III made the conquest of Egypt more feasible.           Amalric led his first expedition into Egypt in 1163, claiming that the Fatimids had not paid the yearly tribute that had begun during the reign of Baldwin III. The vizier, Dirgham, had recently overthrown the vizier ": null
