        " by sea and by land. The siege was long and famine broke out in the Christian camp; the Byzantines and crusaders blamed each other for the failure, and a truce was signed with Saladin. Amalric returned home.     Now Jerusalem was surrounded by hostile enemies. In 1170 Saladin invaded Jerusalem and took the city of ": null
